Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potato{1}(chopped into wedges about the size of your index finger) (no need to peel!) into wedges about the size of your index finger. Pop them on a #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle over a good glug of @oil{}, sprinkle on a pinch of @salt{pinch} and toss to coat. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until browned and slightly crispy, ~{30-35%minutes}.

Meanwhile, put the @British chicken breasts{2} in a #mixing bowl{} and pour over two-thirds of the @BBQ sauce{3}, a good pinch of @salt and a grind of @black pepper{}. Mix together with your hands to ensure the chicken gets a good coating of the sauce. Wrap a rasher of @streaky bacon rasher{2} around each chicken breast and place on a lightly oiled baking tray. If you have any BBQ sauce left in the bowl, scrape it out onto the top of the chicken.

Roast the chicken on the middle shelf of your oven for ~{25-30%minutes}.

> TIP: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Drain and rinse the @cannellini beans{1%can} in a #colander{}. Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and roughly chopped into 1cm pieces) into roughly 1cm pieces. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat, add the onion and cook until soft, ~{5%minutes}. Add the @smoked paprika{1.5%tsp}, stir and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Pour in the @tomato passata{1}, fill the empty carton three-quarters with water and add along with the cannellini beans. Season with a pinch of @salt and @pepper, mix everything together. Simmer gently until reduced, ~{7%minutes}. Remove from the heat, add the @baby spinach{1} and pop a #lid{}. Leave to the side until the spinach has wilted, ~{5-7%minutes}, then stir it through your beans. Taste and add more salt and pepper if it needs it.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}. When the chicken is cooked, remove it from your oven and lower the potato wedges to the middle shelf. Preheat your #grill{} to high. Divide the cheese evenly between each chicken breast, then place under your grill until the cheese is brown and bubbling, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Serve the hunter's chicken with the potato wedges and homemade baked beans on the side and a dollop of the remaining BBQ sauce (not the sauce you mixed with your chicken though!). Enjoy!